00:00:34.053 --> 00:00:35.890
So to find an equation for a line,

00:00:35.890 --> 00:00:37.550
the equation of a line
is gonna be in the form

00:00:37.550 --> 00:00:40.721
y is equal to m-x plus b,

00:00:40.721 --> 00:00:42.251
where m is the slope of the line

00:00:42.251 --> 00:00:44.237
and b is the y-intercept.

00:00:44.237 --> 00:00:46.594
And the slope of the
line, right over here,

00:00:46.594 --> 00:00:50.321
this needs to be equal to
the derivative evaluated

00:00:50.321 --> 00:00:52.097
when x is equal to four.

