two-x over x-squared

00:01:40.244 --> 00:01:43.437
minus three-x and all of that squared.

00:01:43.437 --> 00:01:46.770
And I want to evaluate
what f-prime of four is.

00:01:46.770 --> 00:01:47.930
So, every place where I saw an x,

00:01:47.930 --> 00:01:49.392
I substituted with a four.

00:01:49.392 --> 00:01:51.504
Where I saw the k, k is three.

00:01:51.504 --> 00:01:53.282
And so this is going to be equal to...

00:01:53.282 --> 00:01:56.602
The numerator is three minus
